How to uninstall MySQL Server from Ubuntu 22.04. 


#command to remove MySQL server:
sudo apt-get remove --purge mysql*

#remove the purge:
sudo apt-get purge mysql*

MySQL server is uninstalled completely without leaving residue files:
sudo apt-get autoremove
sudo apt-get autoclean


#after uninstalling applications or packages its good to update the system:
sudo apt-get dist-upgrade

#check the MySQL presence:
mysql --version



